    "full_draft": "A celebration of life at Sunset Cliffs on April 5 — the guitar there not to perform, but to hold the space while people remember. That distinction matters, and the fact that you're thinking about it this carefully, choosing a place that meant something to them and music that would have felt familiar, says everything about how much care is going into this.\n\nThe version of this that goes wrong is a musician who shows up and plays a polished set. What you need is someone who reads the room, scales back when the moment calls for quiet, and never once makes the music the center of attention. That's what I do.\n\nSunset Cliffs is open-air with real wind, so I bring a small, warm-sounding amplifier calibrated low enough to feel acoustic but present enough to carry without competing with the water or the silence. I'm fully self-contained and arrive early.\n\nClassical Guitar — 1 hour: $595\n\nApril 5 is 11 days out. I can hold the date today if you want to move forward.\n\nAlex Guillen\n(619) 755-3246",
